<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="325" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/3485</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Group</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">New
                                        York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-07-27"><hi rend="italic">July 27,
                                1921</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received July 30.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to our letter of June 8th,<note n="61" xml:id="d325fn61">Not printed.</note> we are informed that
                            the Japanese Group have expressed their agreement with the proposal to
                            form a Consortium Council, and it is contemplated that the first meeting
                            may be held some time during the Autumn. The delegates who have been
                            named as comprising the Council are as follows: <list>
                                <item>Mr. T. W. Lamont, for the American Group,</item>
                                <item>Sir Charles S. Addis, for the British Group,</item>
                                <item>Mr. Réné T. de la Chaume, for the French Group, and</item>
                                <item>Mr. T. Okubo, for the Japanese Group.</item>
                            </list></p>
                        <p>Respectfully,</p>
                        <closer><hi rend="smallcaps">J. P. Morgan</hi> &amp; Co.<lb/><hi rend="italic">For the American Group</hi></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>